				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ {h}_{\mathrm{EFSLAT}}=\frac{I_{\mathrm{T}}}{1\mathrm{kW}/{\mathrm{m}}^2} $$\end{document}

The performance ratio (PR) is a system performance index that indicates the overall effect of losses on the array’s rated output due to array temperature, incomplete utilization of the irradiation and system component inefficiencies or failures (IEC 61724). Performance ratios are usually reported on a monthly or yearly basis. A PR value calculated for smaller intervals, such as weekly or daily is useful to identify the occurrences of component failures.8PR=InvO/PAa×IT×ηPanel×100\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ \mathrm{P}\mathrm{R}=\frac{{\mathrm{Inv}}_{O/P}}{A_a\times {I}_T\times {\eta}_{\mathrm{Panel}}}\times 100 $$\end{document}

